summary: This is an internal FBI email chain from July 2021 regarding administrative reminders and trial preparation for the upcoming Ghislaine Maxwell trial. It includes a reference to a detective and special agent prepping witnesses and contains administrative details about work hours and travel.

persons.name: Operational Support Technician
persons.context: Sends administrative reminders to NYO employees regarding WebTA validations, mandatory training, and paperwork deadlines.

events.title: Maxwell Trial Preparation
events.description: Detective and Special Agent are trial prepping several witnesses for the upcoming Maxwell trial.

keyFacts: The email is dated July 13, 2021, during the period leading up to the Ghislaine Maxwell trial.
It references a detective and special agent who are 'trial prepping several witnesses for the upcoming Maxwell trial.'
The document shows internal FBI administrative processes, including time reporting (WebTA), mandatory legal training, and paperwork for Title 18 and TURK sheets.
One individual mentions traveling to Florida for a purpose related to work during the week of July 6-9, 2021.
The correspondence is between FBI personnel in the New York Office (NYO), specifically groups C11 and C20.
